chanisms. The Pa\\beta/Br\\gamma\\ ratio is consistent with optically thick\nemission in LTE at a temperature of ~3500 K, originated from a compact region\nof ~5 Rsun in size: but the line opacity decreases in the Br lines for high\nquantum numbers n_{up}. A good fit to the data is obtained assuming an\nexpanding gas in LTE, with an electron density at the wind base of ~10^13 cm-3.\nIn addition, we find that the observed Brackett ratios are very similar to\nthose reported in previous studies of low-mass CTTSs and Class I sources,\nindicating that these ratios are not dependent on masses and ages. Finally,\nLacc~9 Lsun and Macc~3x10-7 Msun/yr values were found.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Sep 2011 16:13:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-30"}
